          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV",
                "EXTB",
                "GSPEC",
                "STTA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "The excitation functions were measured by activating",
                " stacked gas cells.",
                "Evacuated stainless steel cells diameter 2 cm, length",
                " 2.5 cm closed with 50 um Al windows were filled with",
                " highly enriched 131Xe gas 99.6% up to a pressure of",
                " 0.9 bar.",
                "The cells were irradiated with proton beams of 200 nA",
                " intensity at 28, 24, 20, 15 and 12.5 MeV primary",
                " energies, obtained by changing the accelerator",
                " settings, at the external beam line of the CGR 560",
                " cyclotron of Vrije Universiteit Brussel.",
                "The beam intensity was controlled to keep it constant",
                " within 10% during the irradiations.",
                "The produced Cs isotopes were washed out of the gas",
                " cells.",
                "Total maximal loss in the recovery of Cs radioisotopes",
                " was estimated to be around 3% with an uncertainty of",
                " 2%."
              ]
            }
          ],
